  - name: Greatsword.
    value: ' Melee Weapon Attack: +15 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 22 (4d6
      + 8) slashing damage plus 27 (6d8) radiant damage. '
    category: Actions
  - name: Slaying Longbow.
    value: ' Ranged Weapon Attack: +13 to hit, range 150/600 ft., one target. Hit:
      15 (2d8 + 6) piercing damage plus 27 (6d8) radiant damage. If the target is
      a creature that has 100 hit points or fewer, it must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution
      saving throw or die. '
    category: Actions
  - name: Flying Sword.
    value: ' The solar releases its greatsword to hover magically in an unoccupied
      space within 5 feet of it. If the solar can see the sword, the solar can mentally
      command it as a bonus action to fly up to 50 feet and either make one attack
      against a target or return to the solar''s hands. If the hovering sword is
      targeted by any effect, the solar is considered to be holding it. The hovering
      sword falls if the solar dies. '
    category: Actions
  - name: Healing Touch (4/Day).
    value: ' The solar touches another creature. The target magically regains 40
      (8d8 + 4) hit points and is freed from any curse, disease, poison, blindness,
      or deafness.'
    category: Actions
  - name: other
    value: 'The solar can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below.
      Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end
      of another creature''s turn. The solar regains spent legendary actions at the
      start of its turn. '
    category: Legendary Actions
  - name: Teleport.
    value: ' The solar magically teleports, along with any equipment it is wearing
      or carrying, up to 120 feet to an unoccupied space it can see. '
    category: Legendary Actions
  - name: Searing Burst (Costs 2 Actions).
    value: ' The solar emits magical, divine energy. Each creature of its choice
      in a 10-foot radius must make a DC 23 Dexterity saving throw, taking 14 (4d6)
      fire damage plus 14 (4d6) radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much
      damage on a successful one. '
    category: Legendary Actions
  - name: Blinding Gaze (Costs 3 Actions).
    value: ' The solar targets one creature it can see within 30 feet of it. If the
      target can see it, the target must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw
      or be blinded until magic such as the lesser restoration spell removes the
      blindness.'
    category: Legendary Actions
